UmePlus fonts

UmePlus fonts are modified Ume fonts for Japanese.
http://www.geocities.jp/ep3797/modified_fonts_01.html

I used these fonts for UmePlus fonts:
Kanji = Ume fonts
https://osdn.net/projects/ume-font/releases/
Alphabet/Hiragana/Katakana, Full width alphabet = M+ fonts
https://osdn.net/projects/mplus-fonts/releases/
Thanks to the authors.

License
Ume fonts, M+ fonts:
See docs-{ume,mplus}.
fontforge-scripts:
Public Domain.

Author
UTUMI Hirosi <utuhiro78@yahoo.co.jp>


How to update UmePlus fonts
1. Install fontforge
$ sudo pacman -S fontforge

2. Put the files into umeplus-tmp
$ mkdir umeplus-tmp
$ mv mplus-TESTFLIGHT-062.tar.xz umeplus-tmp/
$ mv umefont_660.7z umeplus-tmp/
$ mv umeplus-fonts-20161108.tar.xz umeplus-tmp/
$ mv umeplus-cl-fonts-20161108.tar.xz umeplus-tmp/

3. Extract the files
$ cd umeplus-tmp/
$ tar xf umeplus-fonts-20161108.tar.xz
$ mv umeplus-fonts-20161108 umeplus-fonts-dev
$ tar xf umeplus-cl-fonts-20161108.tar.xz
$ mv umeplus-cl-fonts-20161108 umeplus-cl-fonts-dev
$ mv umeplus-fonts-dev/update-umeplus-fonts.sh .

4. Update "update-umeplus-fonts.sh"
$ leafpad update-umeplus-fonts.sh

Update these lines:
MPLUSVER="062"
UMEVER="660"
DATE="20161108"

5. Update UmePlus fonts
$ ./update-umeplus-fonts.sh
